---
description: conductor-kit workflow — always-on principles for this repo
alwaysApply: true
---

This repo uses **conductor-kit**. One CLI (`conductor`) is the single entry
point for Jira/GitLab/Git orchestration. The Agent does conversation and
code editing; the CLI does everything deterministic.

1. Never skip the plan gate. After `conductor pick <KEY>`, `.work/{KEY}.md`
   is at `status: plan-draft`. **Do not Edit/Write source files** until the
   user says "approved" and you have run `conductor pick <KEY> --approve`
   (status flips to `plan-approved`). `conductor ship` refuses to run in
   any other state.
2. For every step, invoke the slash command in `.cursor/commands/` — do not
   re-implement the pipeline by hand. Each command delegates to the CLI
   with `--json --agent "Cursor"`.
3. Never `git commit --amend`, `git push --force`, or `--no-verify`. If a
   hook fails, fix the cause and make a new commit.
4. Never edit `.work/{KEY}.md` status lines manually. Let the CLI own
   status transitions.
5. Host-repo conventions live in `.conductor/CONVENTIONS.md`. Read it
   before your first edit in a new session.
